    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-05T09:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-05T09:16:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.7131/103: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-05T16:00:00+01:44"
                            >July 5, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 5—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Department’s telegram 14, July 3, 8 p.m., paragraph (2). Forwarding by the
                    pouch July 7th proposed draft of provisional commercial agreement<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d745fn11">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> similar to that which is being submitted to other countries who have not
                    yet concluded commercial treaties. Five articles provide for general reciprocal
                    most-favored-nation treatment in matters of establishment, commerce, industry,
                    customs, tariff rates, taxes, navigation. Agreement to become effective
                    September 1st and to continue in force until March 1st, 1931. It is in treaty
                    form but clause requiring ratification has been omitted. Am <pb facs="0887"
                        n="793" xml:id="pg_793"/> doubtful however whether in present form it would
                    be valid without Senate approval. Endeavored to secure consent to arrange matter
                    by the exchange of notes but Government considers this method precluded by terms
                    to [<hi rend="italic">of</hi>] Rumanian tariff law.</p>
                <p>Was planning to go on leave July 15th for much needed cure. In view of present
                    circumstances does Department wish me to abandon plan?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
